Eleven people were killed in horror head-on crash on the R37 near The Chuene Resort, Limpopo. JOHANNESBURG - Eleven people have been killed in a head-on collision on the R37 near the Chuene Resort in Limpopo.
Two cars collided at about 6am on Sunday morning, there were no survivors. In KwaZulu-Natal, two mini-bus taxis were involved in a collision on the M25 Curnick Ndlovu Highway in KwaMashu, north of Durban. One person died on the scene and several were injured. Another passenger was seriously injured and had to be airlifted to hospital.